  "issue_title": "wakeword service fails while rest of stack is healthy",
  "issue_body": "## Problem\n\nThe GeniePod stack can otherwise come up healthy, but `genie-wakeword.service` remains failed.\n\nObserved service state from the dashboard/service API:\n\n```text\ncore           healthy\nllm            healthy\napi            healthy\nhealth         healthy\ngovernor       healthy\naudio          healthy\nwhisper        healthy\nhomeassistant  healthy\nwakeword       failed\n```\n\nThis leaves the system usable through the web/API paths, but wake-word activation is broken.\n\n## Why this matters\n\nWake-word should either:\n\n1. start successfully when the local audio/wake-word dependencies are present, or\n2. report a clear disabled/not-configured state when wake-word is intentionally unavailable.\n\nRight now it shows as a failed systemd service while the rest of the stack works, which makes the dashboard look degraded and makes it unclear whether this is an audio-device issue, missing model/script issue, startup ordering issue, or expected disabled behavior.\n\n## Suggested investigation\n\nCollect these on Jetson after a full restart:\n\n```bash\nsystemctl status genie-wakeword --no-pager --lines=80\njournalctl -u genie-wakeword -n 160 --no-pager\nsystemctl status genie-audio genie-whisper --no-pager --lines=40\n/opt/geniepod/bin/detect-audio-device.sh || true\nls -lah /opt/geniepod/bin/genie-wakeword.py /opt/geniepod/bin/genie-wake-listen.py\n```\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- `genie-wakeword.service` starts successfully when wake-word support is configured and available.\n- If wake-word support is not configured or no usable audio input is found, the service/dashboard reports a clear non-failed state or actionable error.\n- Restarting the stack with `genie-restart-all.sh` does not leave wakeword failed when other required services are healthy.",
